<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-11-0976 </DOCNO><TEXT>The aim of this study was to examine the role of the american electricutilities in the development of the alternative energy utilization inthe USA. Federal or local financial incentives combined with a growinginterest of the private utilities in persuading their users to conserveenergy or/and to use alternative energies (together with utility electricity)result in a growing place for alternative energies and energy conservation.Still, since the lowering of the oil prices, a urtain disinterest appeared.</TEXT></DOC>